text: Mount Mahya (, Mahiada) 1031 m, is a mountain in Turkey. It is the highest peak of the Strandzha massif (Yıldız Mountains) in East Thrace, the European part of Turkey. The Amuca tribe a Alevism-Bektashi Yörüks group live there. == Other websites == * Mahya Dağı - map Category:Mountains of Turkey Category:Kırklareli Province
